doctype html
html(lang="en")
  head 
    meta(charset="utf-8")
    meta(name="description" content="Informational site for The Wrongest Words, playable at wrongest.net")
    meta(name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1.0")
    title The Wrongest Website
    link(href="http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Comfortaa:400,700,300" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css")
    link(href="css/wrongest.css" rel="stylesheet")
  body
    section.logo.full-screen
      img.big-logo(src="svg/logo2.svg")  
      .inner
        p A party game where you and your friends struggle to defend the the very stupid statements given to you. Playable on any device with a modern browser, and supports 3-8 players.
        .button-holder
          a.big.button(href="http://www.wrongest.net") Play now
          span ...or keep scrolling to find out how to play.
    section.instructions#HowToPlay
      .inner
        h2 How to play
      figure.phones
        figcaption create and join a game
        img(src="img/phones/setup/create-game.png")
        img(src="img/phones/setup/join-game.png")
        img(src="img/phones/setup/start-game.png")
      .inner
        p Open a browser to 
          strong www.wrongest.net
          | , enter in your name and hit create game. This will give you a unique URL to pass out to your friends. Anyone who goes to that URL will join your lobby. The leader can adjust settings using the gear button, then hit start game when everyone's ready.
      figure.phones
        figcaption start talking crazy!
        img(src="img/phones/gameplay/deal.png")
        img(src="img/phones/gameplay/defend.png")
        img(src="img/phones/gameplay/other-defends.png")
        img(src="img/phones/gameplay/defend-hard.png")
      .inner
        p All players are given a turn, one player is the dealer. When the dealer hits the button, the next player is given a card and a time limit.
        p When you see your card, 
          i it's time to say crazy things.
          |  Your job is try to convince the other players that your statement (which they cannot see) is actually true. It's more fun to to keep the topic itself secret, just dance around the underpinning logic. Which is to say, try to invent some logic.
        p Occasionally, a statement will be marked "hard", that's worth bonus points.
      figure.phones
        figcaption impose judgement
        img(src="img/phones/voting/choose.png")
        img(src="img/phones/voting/chosen.png")
        img(src="img/phones/voting/results.png")
      .inner
        p Now that you've all said stupid things, it's time to make some decisions. You'll be given a list of statements (excluding your own), and you most vote for one 
          i most wrong
          |  and one 
          i least wrong 
          | statement. 
        p Each time your statement is voted 
          i least wrong
          | , you'll get a point. Statements voted 
          i most wrong
          |  are tracked, so that we can pay attention to this sort of thing later.
      figure.phones
        figcaption that's pretty much it.
        img(src="img/phones/gameover/final.png")
      .inner
        p Gameplay continues like this until we can declare a winner and the wrongest statement. I think you've got the idea by now, so how about you...
        .button-holder
          a.big.button(href="http://www.wrongest.net") play the wrongest words